biscuit cutter (Ø 6 cm) into flour to prevent dough from sticking, cut out biscuits by pushing cutter into dough starting around outside edges and working towards centre.  Gently press remaining dough together and repeat process."},{"content":"Place biscuits in prepared baking tin so they are just touching and bake for 15-20 minutes (230°C) until golden brown."},{"content":"Wrap biscuits in a clean kitchen towel to keep warm before serving."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Gravy"},{"content":"Place crumbled pieces of sausagemeat, butter, flour, salt and pepper in mixing bowl then, without measuring cup, cook <b>8-10 min\/120°C\/\/speed <b>."},{"content":"Add milk through hole in mixing bowl lid, insert measuring cup and cook <b>15 min\/100°C\/\/speed 2<b>."},{"content":"Serve gravy immediately over fresh warm biscuits."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Be careful not to over handle the dough, as this will make the biscuits tough.","Instead of rolling out the dough with a rolling pin, use your hands to shape it.","For easy removal of dough, place mixing bowl upside down on your lightly floured surface and twist the black flower shape at the base of the blades clockwise. Dough will fall from the mixing bowl onto floured surface. Use spatula to remove any remaining dough from the mixing bowl.","Pre-freeze butter and shortening in zip lock bags so biscuits are even easier to prepare next time."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","40m","9 portions"]}